President Obama called Prime Minister Haidar Al-Abadi of Iraq to congratulate him on the recent successes of Iraqi forces in Ramadi and to express ongoing support in the fight against ISIL. The President praised the courage and tenacity of the Iraqi Security Forces and assured continued support from the United States and the counter-ISIL Coalition. They discussed plans to stabilize Ramadi and create conditions for residents to return home. President Obama also emphasized the U.S. commitment to help Iraq stabilize and strengthen its economy. The need for improved maintenance work on Mosul Dam was highlighted. They also expressed concern over Saudi Arabia's execution of Sheikh Nimr Al-Nimr and agreed on the importance of restraint and diplomatic engagement to avoid worsening sectarian tensions. President Obama reiterated the U.S. commitment to Iraq's territorial integrity and called on Turkey to withdraw any unauthorized military forces. Both leaders reaffirmed their commitment to the strategic partnership between the United States and Iraq in the fight against ISIL.